# Implementation Plan - Reservation Approval Workflow & Notifications

This plan upgrades the Reservation system from an informal planning tool into a **Managed Planning Lifecycle**. This allows employees to propose tentative dates that managers can explicitly "Acknowledge" or "Approve," providing high-level clearance before a formal leave application is submitted.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change introduces a new "Pending Approval" state for reservations.
> - **Constraint**: Reservations will **not** deduct from leave balances even after approval.
> - **Chain**: I am proposing a simplified **Single-Level Approval** (Direct Manager / OM) for reservations to keep them faster than formal requests. **Is a single-level approval sufficient for reservations?**

## Proposed Changes

### Database Schema

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add fields to `Reservation` model:
    - `status`: Update to include `PENDING`, `APPROVED`, `REJECTED`.
    - `approverId`: The ID of the manager who handled it.
    - `handledAt`: Timestamp of decision.
    - `rejectionReason`: Optional feedback.

### Backend - Controller Improvements

#### [MODIFY] [reservation.controller.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/controllers/reservation.controller.ts)
- Update `createReservation`: Set initial status to `PENDING`.
- Add `approveReservation(id)` endpoint.
- Add `rejectReservation(id)` endpoint.
- Integrate Notification and Email triggers at each step.

### Backend - Notification & Email Service

#### [MODIFY] [email.service.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/services/email.service.ts)
- **Approver Notification**: Email sent to HOD/OM when a new reservation is "Available for Approval."
- **Requester Update**: Email sent to Employee when their reservation is "Approved" or "Rejected."

#### [MODIFY] [notification.controller.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/controllers/notification.controller.ts)
- Create in-app notifications for the same events.

### Frontend - UI Updates

#### [MODIFY] [CalendarView.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/pages/CalendarView.tsx)
- Update status colors for reservations (e.g., Orange for Pending, Green-Striped for Approved).
- Add "Approval" action buttons for managers.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Postman test: Create reservation -> Check `Notification` table for manager alert.
- Postman test: Approve reservation -> Check `Notification` table for employee update.

### Manual Verification
- Log in as Employee -> Create Reservation.
- Log in as OM -> View dashboard notification -> Approve reservation.
- Log back in as Employee -> Verify status change on calendar/dashboard.
